I am writing in response to Dr George Manyali’s treatise published in DN, December 24, 2020 titled, ‘PhD by publication enhances the quality of scientific work’. In the article, he rightly reports that for a long time, universities have awarded PhDs to students on the basis of publication in peer-reviewed journals.



